cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on applying deep reinforcement learning to a robotic arm in a human-robot interaction task. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of an environment model to accelerate learning. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses deep reinforcement learning and discusses the use of synthetic data to improve learning efficiency. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a learned model to produce optimal plans in real world applications. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the task involves interpreting human gestures as actions for the robotic arm to perform.
